Life and today
is the first day
of the rest of mine.

17:32.886 --> 17:34.626
You sound like
a fortune cookie.

17:34.721 --> 17:37.758
No. I sound like
a woman with a future.

17:37.933 --> 17:40.390
Is there something
you're not telling me?

17:40.477 --> 17:42.684
I took the test.

17:42.771 --> 17:44.136
Are you pregnant?

17:45.232 --> 17:50.022
No! Girl, now, how am I
gonna be pregnant wearing
this outfit two shifts a day?

17:50.111 --> 17:53.979
The management
training program.
I took the test.

17:54.074 --> 17:55.655
Oh, that.

17:56.660 --> 17:58.742
What do you mean,
"Oh, that"?

17:58.828 --> 18:02.116
Nothing. ljust think
you shouldn't get
your hopes up, that's all.

18:02.207 --> 18:04.914
Only a fool would put money
on a one-in-5O chance.

18:05.001 --> 18:07.583
Look, if I make manager,
I can earn enough money

18:07.671 --> 18:09.582
to go back
to school,
get my degree.

18:09.673 --> 18:12.289
I can move
my family
out of here.

18:12.384 --> 18:14.921
It's not right,
one storm comes
rolling through here

18:15.011 --> 18:17.548
and blows away
my whole life.

18:17.639 --> 18:22.303
My mother,
my college education,
my dreams.

18:25.355 --> 18:26.765
I'm sorry.

18:27.649 --> 18:31.107
It's just you've been talking
like this since we were
in kindergarten.

18:31.194 --> 18:34.436
One scheme after another,
and nothing ever happens.

18:38.994 --> 18:43.033
What in the world?
Where did you learn
to do that?

18:48.837 --> 18:52.125
I don't...
Monica, let me talk
to you for a sec.

19:03.601 --> 19:07.469
I'm sorry, Monica.
You're just not qualified
for the management program.

19:07.564 --> 19:09.600
So I didn't do well
on the test?

19:09.691 --> 19:11.147
You did fine.

19:11.234 --> 19:13.225
Not top tier, but...
But what?

19:13.320 --> 19:17.108
I'm motivated and
I'm hardworking. Mr. Lamont,
I've never missed a day.

19:17.198 --> 19:18.449
That's not the issue.

19:18.533 --> 19:19.818
A management position means

19:19.909 --> 19:22.776
you need to be to be available
for any location in the state.

19:22.871 --> 19:26.079
And it's just not right
for someone
in your situation.

19:26.166 --> 19:27.201
My situation?

19:27.292 --> 19:28.372
Your home life.

19:28.460 --> 19:30.371
Your brother,
your grandmother.
That's the point!

19:30.462 --> 19:33.204
I'm the breadwinner.
I need the money. And...

19:33.298 --> 19:35.664
I mean,
I can't make hamburgers
for the rest of my life.

19:35.759 --> 19:39.126
You're good
at yourjob, Monica.
What's wrong with that?

19:39.220 --> 19:40.801
And you should be
happy you have one.

19:40.889 --> 19:43.756
There's a lot of people
in this city who don't.

19:44.809 --> 19:46.140
(SCOFFS)

19:48.938 --> 19:51.190
I thought for dessert,

19:51.274 --> 19:55.392
we could go to that
adorable yogurt place
near the bus depot.

19:57.280 --> 20:00.738
lcant.lhave
to go to the library
for a research paper.

20:00.825 --> 20:04.158
The library?
Haven't you ever
heard of the Internet?

20:06.081 --> 20:11.041
Actually, the research paper
is on libraries and how
during the digital age

20:11.127 --> 20:14.790
they're becoming
increasingly obsolete
for our generation.

20:17.258 --> 20:19.214
Do you need a lift?

20:19.302 --> 20:20.291
What?

20:20.387 --> 20:21.547
Your car.

20:21.638 --> 20:23.845
It got stolen. Remember?

20:27.310 --> 20:28.925
So do you?

20:29.020 --> 20:31.011
That's okay.
I think I'm just
gonna walk.

20:31.106 --> 20:32.312
Okay.

20:52.377 --> 20:53.492
Hi.

20:54.379 --> 20:55.494
Hi.

21:08.810 --> 21:12.553
The photo's gotta be
in here somewhere.
It's a group shot.

21:12.647 --> 21:14.012
Maybe 10, 12 people.

21:14.107 --> 21:15.096
What kind of group is it?

21:15.191 --> 21:18.604
It was a party or a meeting.
My parents were in it.

21:19.362 --> 21:21.444
Kaito Nakamura.
You knew Nakamura?

21:21.531 --> 21:22.771
No. My folks did.

21:22.866 --> 21:24.276
He use to come over
the house sometimes.

21:24.367 --> 21:26.028
My father didn't seem
to care for him too much.

21:26.119 --> 21:27.325
I remember
the last time
I saw him,

21:27.412 --> 21:31.155
my Mom hugged him,
and it lasted just
a little bit too long.

21:31.624 --> 21:33.034
What about
the others
in the group?

21:33.126 --> 21:34.662
Linderman was in it.

21:34.752 --> 21:36.617
Charles Deveaux, too.

21:38.506 --> 21:40.622
A lot of them are dead now.

21:42.260 --> 21:44.046
These your boys?

21:46.514 --> 21:47.720
Yeah.

21:49.392 --> 21:50.893
What? You don't
see them that often?
Look, I don't...

21:50.977 --> 21:54.014
I'm sorry,
I don't really
know you that well.

21:54.105 --> 21:58.064
My wife...
My ex-wife
cheated on me.

21:59.944 --> 22:01.400
Which I could have
forgiven her for,

22:01.488 --> 22:05.197
except for that fact
that she was pregnant
with his baby.

22:05.325 --> 22:07.737
Why are you
telling me
all this?

22:07.827 --> 22:11.115
ljust... I know a bunch
of stuff about you,
I figured it's only fair.

22:11.206 --> 22:13.492
If you wanna unload,
go ahead.

22:15.835 --> 22:18.793
Six months ago,
I was a cop in LA.
Married.

22:19.964 --> 22:22.671
Expecting a child.
And all of a sudden
this stuff started happening.

22:22.759 --> 22:25.421
It just turned
everything
upside down.

22:25.595 --> 22:27.927
(SIGHING) I'm just
looking for answers.

22:32.769 --> 22:34.600
Maybe this will help.

22:40.401 --> 22:41.652
MATT: That's the same photo.

22:41.736 --> 22:42.896
NATHAN: Half the people
in this picture are dead.

22:42.987 --> 22:44.693
It's like the killer's
picking off one by one.

22:44.781 --> 22:46.737
Maybe one of these
is the killer.

22:46.866 --> 22:48.527
NATHAN: Look,
here's my father.
This is my mother.

22:48.618 --> 22:51.781
Charles Deveaux,
Linderman,
Kaito Nakamura.

22:51.871 --> 22:54.157
This guy's name is Bob.

22:54.290 --> 22:56.121
Bob. I don't know
his last name.

22:56.209 --> 22:59.121
I don't know
the rest of the people
in that picture, either.

22:59.212 --> 23:00.452
MATT: I know him.

23:00.547 --> 23:01.662
How?

23:05.134 --> 23:06.795
That's my father.

23:23.820 --> 23:24.980
CAMILLE: Hey.

23:26.489 --> 23:29.276
"Making hamburgers."
Is he kidding me?

23:29.367 --> 23:31.574
I swear, I'd like
to smack him
upside his head.

23:31.661 --> 23:35.028
I'm glad you didn't.
You can't afford
to get fired.

23:35.123 --> 23:38.581
I can't explain it,
but I know I'm supposed
to be somebody.

23:38.668 --> 23:41.751
I feel like there's
something inside me
that wants to come out.

23:41.838 --> 23:44.250
Does that make any sense?

23:44.340 --> 23:46.831
You lost more than
most in the storm.

23:46.926 --> 23:51.511
And that kind of loss,
it takes a while. You
shouldn't be in such a hurry.

23:53.057 --> 23:55.434
I don't know.
Maybe God's
punishing me.

23:55.518 --> 23:57.975
Now, why would he do that?

23:58.062 --> 23:59.222
For being selfish.

24:00.064 --> 24:04.103
I pray for it every Sunday
in church. For God
to find me a way out of here.

24:04.193 --> 24:07.981
Everybody else is praying
for the community,
to put things back together,

24:08.072 --> 24:10.734
to give them
strength. Not me.

24:10.825 --> 24:13.316
I'm just praying
for a way out.

24:14.912 --> 24:16.743
That's terrible, isn't it?

24:16.831 --> 24:21.700
Monica, given the situation,
I'd say it's pretty normal.

24:22.587 --> 24:23.827
Normal.

24:25.882 --> 24:28.043
Yeah.
That's me,
all right.

24:30.219 --> 24:34.383
I offer to take you anywhere,
and this is all you can
come up with.

24:35.892 --> 24:38.383
(CHUCKLES)
What can I say?
I'm a cheap date.

24:40.229 --> 24:42.720
WEST: You've got
a thing for heights, huh?

24:43.650 --> 24:46.983
There was this place
near where I used
to live in Texas.

24:47.070 --> 24:52.406
There was this
old gravel tower. I used to
climb up to the top of it.

24:54.202 --> 24:56.067
See what I could do.

24:57.914 --> 24:59.450
You'd jump off?

25:00.750 --> 25:01.910
Yeah.

25:03.086 --> 25:06.874
I guess I've just
been thinking
a lot about my life.

25:07.757 --> 25:10.089
How it all
went away so fast.

25:11.177 --> 25:13.088
And why did it go away?

25:14.681 --> 25:16.592
I can't tell you that.

25:17.308 --> 25:19.424
The truth is,
so many terrible things
happened to me

25:19.519 --> 25:21.305
While I lived there.

25:23.189 --> 25:26.522
I'm not sure I could
ever open up
to anyone again.

25:28.611 --> 25:30.693
Well, we're here together.

25:31.406 --> 25:34.273
So part of you
must want to
share something.

25:35.660 --> 25:37.446
I want to trust you.

25:39.288 --> 25:40.698
Then jump.

25:41.791 --> 25:42.826
What?

25:42.917 --> 25:44.453
Trust begins
with a leap.

25:44.544 --> 25:46.159
Cheesy but true.

25:46.254 --> 25:47.289
No. It'll be gross.

25:47.380 --> 25:48.916
My arms pop out
of their sockets.

25:49.006 --> 25:51.873
And sometimes my feet
come out facing each other.

25:51.968 --> 25:53.208
(WHISPERING)
It's not cute.

25:53.302 --> 25:56.385
Claire, these
fears you have,

25:57.640 --> 26:00.848
of someone
finding out
aboutyou,

26:01.519 --> 26:03.680
of feeling
different forever,

26:04.188 --> 26:05.974
I have them too.

26:06.899 --> 26:08.150
You can
share them
with me.

26:08.234 --> 26:11.647
But I can't help you
if you don't trust me.

26:15.491 --> 26:16.697
(WHISPERING) Okay.

26:43.811 --> 26:45.426
You caught me.

26:45.521 --> 26:46.681
Of course I did.

26:47.273 --> 26:49.389
But I would have been fine.

26:49.984 --> 26:51.770
I know
you can heal, Claire.

26:52.487 --> 26:54.569
But I never want to
see you hurt.

27:10.630 --> 27:12.040
(DISTORTED VOICE ON TV)

27:14.509 --> 27:17.876
I don't understand.
You don't even have tools.

27:17.970 --> 27:21.258
Just hold on.
Almost got it.

27:21.891 --> 27:25.759
You know, if this
doesn't work, you're dead.
You know that, right?

27:31.234 --> 27:33.145
(STA TIC BUZZ/NG)

27:36.405 --> 27:38.270
Wow, you did it!

27:38.366 --> 27:40.277
(ANNOUNCER CHATTER/NG ON TV)

27:40.993 --> 27:43.154
All right,
you got your stay
of execution.

27:43.246 --> 27:44.577
(LAUGHS)

27:45.414 --> 27:47.075
(CHEER/NG ON TV)

27:56.801 --> 27:58.257
Is that Pay-Per-View?

27:58.344 --> 27:59.584
Uh-huh.

28:00.054 --> 28:01.919
How did you get that?

28:02.181 --> 28:05.924
Turns out Micah's
some type of genius
and rigged the cable.

28:08.187 --> 28:09.688
Is that true?

28:10.606 --> 28:12.267
Yeah. I'm sorry.

28:18.072 --> 28:19.573
(SIGHING)

28:25.204 --> 28:27.286
I was just
trying to help.

28:29.959 --> 28:33.167
Look, I know it's tough,
being stuck with
your cousins like this.

28:33.254 --> 28:35.711
After everything
you've been through.

28:35.798 --> 28:38.039
But I promised your mother
that I'd look after you,

28:38.134 --> 28:41.171
so you gotta obey
the rules around here.
Okay?

28:41.929 --> 28:43.135
I know.

28:44.432 --> 28:46.969
I got dinner for you guys.

28:49.645 --> 28:51.977
You can eat
in front of the TV.

28:54.066 --> 28:55.397
(EXHALES)

29:14.378 --> 29:16.539
Hey. Are you okay?

29:17.506 --> 29:18.666
Yeah.

29:19.342 --> 29:22.379
ljust wish I could
fix your dreams for you.

29:24.513 --> 29:26.344
You're a sweet kid.

29:26.974 --> 29:29.215
Go tell Damon
dinner's ready.

29:30.436 --> 29:31.892
Dinner's ready.

29:31.979 --> 29:33.685
Yeah. In a minute.

29:35.399 --> 29:37.435
Here goes the 619.

29:37.526 --> 29:38.857
Oh!

29:38.903 --> 29:42.111
ANNOUNCER:
That’s worth seeing again.
That's awesome.

29:55.920 --> 29:56.955
Matt. You're home!

29:57.046 --> 29:59.583
(LAUGHING) Hey.
Yeah. I'm home.

30:00.549 --> 30:04.041
I need to talk to you.
Both of you, actually.

30:04.136 --> 30:05.251
Is everything, okay?

30:05.346 --> 30:06.381
Yeah. Yeah.

30:08.891 --> 30:10.631
l have to find my father.

30:10.893 --> 30:12.303
You don't know
where your dad is?

30:12.561 --> 30:14.722
He left me
when lwas 13.

30:15.731 --> 30:18.768
He gave me $120
and a pat on the head.

30:18.859 --> 30:19.985
And you haven't
seen him since?

30:20.069 --> 30:21.525
I've tried, but...

30:21.612 --> 30:25.400
That's the thing
about criminals, they
don't like to be found.

30:25.491 --> 30:26.822
He's a bad guy?

30:26.909 --> 30:30.197
My dad stole a lot of money
from a lot of people.

30:30.287 --> 30:31.538
And the case
I'm working on
right now,

30:31.622 --> 30:34.409
I have a feeling that
he's in the middle of
something really dangerous

30:34.500 --> 30:38.368
and I need to talk to him,
so I need you
to help me find him.

30:40.089 --> 30:41.169
Okay?

30:41.257 --> 30:43.248
Okay.
All right. Good.

30:46.345 --> 30:48.586
There he is.
That's my dad.

30:50.599 --> 30:52.726
Molly, what is it?

30:52.810 --> 30:53.845
Molly, what's wrong?

30:53.936 --> 30:55.642
Put it away.
Put it away.

30:55.730 --> 30:57.220
Molly...
Molly, what's wrong?

30:57.314 --> 30:59.851
Please don't make me
look for him. Please
don't make me look.

30:59.942 --> 31:01.603
I don't understand.
Why not?

31:01.694 --> 31:03.525
(WHISPERING)
He's the man
in my dreams.

31:03.612 --> 31:05.694
He is the nightmare man.

31:38.856 --> 31:41.313
I'm gonna
make things
right, Pete.

31:49.200 --> 31:51.031
(SHOUTING)
You get away
from me.

32:08.469 --> 32:09.800
(GIGGLES)

32:10.471 --> 32:13.304
Oh my gosh,
look what time it is.
My dad's gonna kill me.

32:13.390 --> 32:15.255
What lie did you use
to get out of the house?

32:15.351 --> 32:17.091
'Cause I'm guessing
you didn't say
you were flying around

32:17.186 --> 32:18.972
in the arms
of some kid
from school.

32:19.063 --> 32:21.725
I said I was going
to the library.

32:21.816 --> 32:23.056
Ouch.

32:23.150 --> 32:24.981
(LAUGHS) I'm sure
he didn't suspect
a thing.

32:25.069 --> 32:27.310
I'm sorry,
I'm a lousy liar.

32:27.404 --> 32:30.191
Look, if we're going
to keep seeing each other,

32:30.282 --> 32:31.567
you've got to come up
with something good.

32:31.659 --> 32:33.445
Something consistent.
Like what?

32:33.536 --> 32:35.401
I'm volunteering
at a soup kitchen?

32:35.496 --> 32:39.330
Claire, the credible lies
are the ones
that make you look bad.

32:39.500 --> 32:42.867
What else is it
that your dad doesn't
want you to do?

32:44.380 --> 32:46.541
I think I have
just the thing.

32:46.632 --> 32:49.169
Aren't you going
to say good night?

32:57.059 --> 32:58.765
You're killing me.

32:58.853 --> 33:00.389
(SNICKERS)

33:03.649 --> 33:05.150
(BLEATING)

33:05.234 --> 33:07.225
(LAT/N MUSIC ON RAD/O)

33:20.332 --> 33:21.583
Gabriel.

33:22.376 --> 33:24.207
Here. Check this out.

33:27.089 --> 33:30.752
There are killers
in the car with us.

33:30.885 --> 33:32.125
(LAUGHING) What?

33:32.219 --> 33:34.631
"Homicidio, "
right there.

33:38.893 --> 33:41.100
Well, golly,
they seem so...

33:41.187 --> 33:44.850
Dude, I've been riding
with them for two days.

33:46.734 --> 33:48.565
We gotta ditch them.

33:50.112 --> 33:51.443
Okay...

33:53.824 --> 33:57.737
All right, I'll distract them.
You go call the police.

33:57.828 --> 34:00.285
There's a pay phone
right inside.

34:11.675 --> 34:13.415
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

34:17.139 --> 34:19.130
We have a problem.

34:19.225 --> 34:21.887
I need to ask you a question,
and you need
to tell me the truth.

34:21.977 --> 34:23.057
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

34:23.145 --> 34:25.136
What is it?
This.

34:25.731 --> 34:27.187
Is this you?

34:33.489 --> 34:37.198
Yes. This is us.
But it is not our fault.

34:38.661 --> 34:41.027
We didn't mean
to hurt anyone.

34:42.039 --> 34:44.781
Well, you can tell the police
that because Derek
is calling them right now.

34:44.875 --> 34:47.252
No,no,no.
Please, no.
He cannot.

34:47.336 --> 34:49.201
(BOTH SPEAKING SPANISH)

34:51.423 --> 34:53.209
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

34:53.300 --> 34:54.756
(GASPING)

34:55.511 --> 34:56.500
Maya.

34:57.596 --> 34:59.632
What are you
doing to me?

35:20.661 --> 35:24.245
You both have power.

35:25.582 --> 35:27.538
(CRYING) This is
not our fault.

35:28.419 --> 35:30.831
We don't know
what's happening
to us.

35:30.921 --> 35:33.503
That's why you need
to find Dr. Suresh.

35:33.590 --> 35:34.750
Yes.

35:36.176 --> 35:38.918
Believe me, I understand
what you're going through.

35:39.013 --> 35:43.632
To be held responsible
for things that you didn't
mean to do, being hunted.

35:44.810 --> 35:46.801
I've helped Suresh with
so many people like you.

35:46.895 --> 35:48.806
He'll know what to do.

35:48.897 --> 35:50.398
The police.

35:52.901 --> 35:55.062
They have to catch us first.

35:56.113 --> 35:57.853
(ENGINE STARTING)

36:25.768 --> 36:27.599
How was the library?

36:28.103 --> 36:29.092
(SIGHING)

36:29.188 --> 36:31.144
Dad, I can explain.

36:31.231 --> 36:32.266
You don't need to.

36:33.025 --> 36:34.640
You were with a boy.

36:34.735 --> 36:37.101
No. No. There's no boy.

36:39.156 --> 36:41.738
Okay. So?

36:43.285 --> 36:44.695
I'm waiting.

36:46.455 --> 36:48.821
I tried out
for cheerleading.

36:49.541 --> 36:51.372
Cheerleading?
I made the squad.

36:51.460 --> 36:56.295
I forged your signature on
the release form. The girls
took me out to celebrate.

36:59.301 --> 37:02.043
First you get
your car stolen,
now this. I...

37:02.179 --> 37:04.215
I told you,
no cheerleading.

37:04.306 --> 37:05.967
I was
very specific
about that.

37:06.058 --> 37:09.050
Dad, cheerleading
makes me happy, okay?

37:09.144 --> 37:12.432
Look, I know it's scary
and I know there are risks.
Just please,

37:12.523 --> 37:14.809
let me have this one thing.

37:14.900 --> 37:16.561
I've done everything else
you've asked me to.

37:16.652 --> 37:19.439
I've given up
my friends
and my life.

37:19.530 --> 37:22.146
I just need
one thing
that's normal.

37:26.078 --> 37:29.570
I had no idea
that cheerleading meant
that much to you.

37:31.333 --> 37:33.324
Took me by surprise, too.

37:39.007 --> 37:41.043
You're gonna
let me do it?

37:46.098 --> 37:48.009
I'll make you a deal.

37:49.810 --> 37:51.346
You cheerlead.

37:52.604 --> 37:56.062
But you promise me
that you will not date.

37:57.192 --> 37:58.773
For now.

38:01.530 --> 38:02.770
Okay.

38:04.575 --> 38:05.781
Okay.

38:12.499 --> 38:14.000
(SIGHING)

38:16.712 --> 38:18.168
(CHIMING)

38:33.896 --> 38:37.388
I have a lead
on the paintings.
We have to go to Odessa.

38:38.692 --> 38:39.647
Texas?

38:39.735 --> 38:40.815
No. Ukraine.

38:43.322 --> 38:46.610
It's a long trip.
What will you tell
your family?

38:48.285 --> 38:50.742
I'm sure
I'll think
of something.

38:59.379 --> 39:01.756
(WHISPERING)
She's finally
settling down.

39:01.840 --> 39:03.546
I'm sorry.

39:04.468 --> 39:05.548
You didn't know.

39:05.636 --> 39:09.470
No. I'm sorry because
Molly has to find my father.

39:09.556 --> 39:11.763
That is out of the question.

39:13.268 --> 39:16.226
A lot of people
in this photo
are dead.

39:16.313 --> 39:18.053
This guy, dead.
This guy, dead.

39:18.148 --> 39:20.685
Kaito Nakamura, murdered.
Angela Petrelli, attacked.

39:20.776 --> 39:22.516
This is my dad.
He may already
be dead.

39:22.611 --> 39:24.442
He may be the next victim.
He may be the killer.

39:24.530 --> 39:26.566
I have to find that out.

39:27.616 --> 39:30.153
Okay. This man here,
this is the man I work for.

39:30.244 --> 39:32.610
His name is Bob.
I'll take you to him.

39:32.704 --> 39:33.910
Fine.

39:33.997 --> 39:35.112
After we find my dad.

39:35.207 --> 39:36.242
You leave Molly
out of this.

39:36.333 --> 39:38.665
You are asking
a little girl to confront
her worst nightmare.

39:38.752 --> 39:41.585
Maybe confronting it
is exactly what she needs.

39:41.672 --> 39:43.037
So this is all
about helping Molly?

39:43.131 --> 39:44.871
Because to me it sounds
like a 13-year-old boy

39:44.967 --> 39:46.127
trying to make
his daddy pay
for leaving him.

39:46.218 --> 39:48.675
And you know everything
about daddy issues.

39:48.762 --> 39:50.218
Yeah, I do.

39:52.683 --> 39:55.925
I'll do it for you, Matt.
I'll find your father.

39:59.648 --> 40:00.979
Thank you.

40:14.204 --> 40:15.614
Monica, it's dead tonight.

40:15.706 --> 40:18.743
Let's close up.
You get the front door,
I'll get the back.

40:18.834 --> 40:20.074
Sure.

40:27.843 --> 40:29.458
Sorry, we're closed.

40:29.553 --> 40:31.760
The sign says
y'all close at 10:00.
Look, I'm hungry.

40:31.847 --> 40:34.930
My boss, he's making me
close up for the night.

40:35.017 --> 40:36.302
And I said I'm hungry.

40:36.393 --> 40:38.600
And while you're at it,
I'll take everything
you got in the register.

40:38.687 --> 40:39.676
Okay, okay.

40:39.771 --> 40:41.181
Sit down right there!

40:59.374 --> 41:00.989
(GRUNTING)

41:09.259 --> 41:10.669
(GRUNTS)

41:12.387 --> 41:14.173
Did you just see...

41:14.264 --> 41:15.800
Where did you learn that?

41:17.225 --> 41:18.476
On TV.

41:20.979 --> 41:21.968
MOHINDER:
We're right here
for you.

41:22.064 --> 41:24.726
MATT: Yeah.
We're gonna
protect you.

41:33.575 --> 41:35.076
I see a city.

41:37.871 --> 41:39.736
Philadelphia. Good.

41:44.086 --> 41:45.747
An apartment building.
MATT: What floor?

41:45.837 --> 41:46.826
I don't want to go in.

41:46.922 --> 41:49.413
He can't hurt you.
It's okay.

41:51.051 --> 41:52.507
Third floor.
MATT: Okay, good.

41:52.594 --> 41:54.926
Good. What's
apartment number?

41:56.139 --> 41:57.390
He knows I'm here.
He's coming.

41:57.474 --> 42:00.637
Okay, Molly.
What apartment?
Quickly. Come on.

42:01.061 --> 42:02.346
Nine.
Nine. Good girl.

42:02.437 --> 42:05.099
All right,
get out of there,
right now.

42:05.982 --> 42:07.108
He sees me...

42:07.150 --> 42:08.185
Leave me alone.
Molly, Molly.
Get out of there.

42:08.276 --> 42:09.311
Leave me alone.

42:09.444 --> 42:12.402
No!No!No!
Molly! Molly!

42:14.950 --> 42:15.939
Matt...

42:17.786 --> 42:19.697
MOHINDER: Molly? Molly?
Molly?

42:20.414 --> 42:22.154
She's breathing.
What happened?

42:22.249 --> 42:23.284
She's in shock.
She won't wake up.

42:23.375 --> 42:24.831
Come on.
Molly, you did it.
It's time to get up.

42:24.918 --> 42:26.158
MOHINDER: Matt, don't.
Molly, it's time to get up.

42:26.253 --> 42:27.368
MOHINDER: Matt, don't.
Come on. Wake up.

42:27.462 --> 42:28.577
Don't...

42:28.672 --> 42:30.628
MOLLY: Matt, help me!

42:33.135 --> 42:34.124
Matt!
